===Etymology===
Possibly {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*b-s-lu}} ({{zh-ref|STEDT}}) and cognate to {{cog|bo|སླུས|gloss=to entice; to impose on; to deceive}}. The character {{l|zh|䛻}} would have been phonetically closer to {{och-l|盾}} ~ {{IPAchar|/*slun/}} at an early stage, which might have been an internal cognate, but it was normalized as an alternative form of {{m-self|zh|誘}} by later lexicographers. Also related to {{och-l|訹}}. ({{zh-ref|Wang, 2012}})

